{
  "name": "register-uploaded-dropped-20260406-2144",
  "idea": "Register uploaded/dropped videos as generations in the database, same as images.\n\n## The gap\nImages: uploadImageGeneration \u2192 creates generations row \u2192 gets generationId \u2192 lightbox/shots work\nVideos: uploadAsset \u2192 stores raw file \u2192 no generationId \u2192 lightbox/shots broken\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Add uploadVideoGeneration in useAssetManagement.ts \u2014 mirrors uploadImageGeneration. Upload to media bucket, extract thumbnail from first frame via videoThumbnailGenerator.ts, call createExternalUploadGeneration with type:'video'. Return same shape as image upload.\n\n2. Add isVideoFile helper in external-drop-utils.ts (parallel to isImageFile). Route video files through new path in handleFileDrop: isImageFile \u2192 existing, isVideoFile \u2192 new uploadVideoGeneration path, else \u2192 existing uploadAsset.\n\n3. Update AssetPanel upload flow \u2014 route video files through generation path too.\n\n4. Wire uploadVideoGeneration through hook interfaces: useAssetManagement \u2192 useExternalDrop \u2192 external-drop-utils.\n\n## Key files\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useAssetManagement.ts \u2014 add uploadVideoGeneration\n- src/tools/video-editor/lib/external-drop-utils.ts \u2014 add isVideoFile, update handleFileDrop\n- src/tools/video-editor/hooks/useExternalDrop.ts \u2014 wire through\n- src/integrations/supabase/repositories/generationMutationsRepository.ts \u2014 has createExternalUploadGeneration (already generic)\n- src/shared/lib/media/videoThumbnailGenerator.ts \u2014 extractThumbnailFromVideo for first frame\n- src/tools/video-editor/components/PropertiesPanel/AssetPanel.tsx \u2014 upload button\n\n## Key constraint\n- generationId field is optional on AssetRegistryEntry so existing videos without it keep working\n- media bucket may have size limits \u2014 check and handle\n- Thumbnail extraction can fail for some codecs \u2014 use try/catch with fallback",
